mountains of colorado wyoming and utah and in eastern parts of the 
lake superior snowbelt 
new england expected colder windier weather today lows of 
between 10 and 15 are expected tonight in northeastern new york and 
northern vermont 
snow advisories were posted today in the mountains of northern 
and central colorado northern wyoming where up to eight inches 
of snow are possible and northern utah where up to a halffoot 
of snow is predicted by this morning 
the great lakes area expects partly cloudy blustery weather and 
lower temperatures today 
a highpressure front is expected to spawn sunshine and colder 
temperatures in wisconsin the national weather service says 
a cold front tuesday night spread snow across the central 
rockies showers along the front extended from northern california 
and southern oregon to south dakota and nebraska snow fell in the 
higher elevations while light rain and drizzle prevailed in lower 
altitudes 
clouds covered much of the northeast tuesday with snow showers 
in the great lakes region freezing rain pelted parts of the upper 
