<TEXT>
cheating in india has forced the educational 
testing service to reschedule a graduate test cancel an english 
proficiency test and wipe out the test scores of nearly 3000 
students 
ets spokesman ray nicosia said it was uncertain if the cheating 
announced wednesday was the largestscale breach of standardized 
test security ever but such cases have rarely extended beyond a 
single class school or test center 
nicosia said ets based in princeton nj had received about 
50 letters from indian students and test center supervisors 
indicating that students had been able to buy copies of the 
standardized tests before the administration dates 
ets said it had learned that test materials had been improperly 
obtained in advance by students for the oct 28 test of english as 
a foreign language this prompted cancellation of exams at five 
centers in the bangalore area affecting 620 students according to 
ets 
the language exam taken annually by 500000 students worldwide 
including 21500 indian students is designed to evaluate english 
proficiency in students whose native language is not english it is 
used for admission by 3000 north american colleges and 
universities 
an investigation also found students were able to buy copies of 
the graduate record examination before taking last months test 
the test is taken primarily by college students to enter 
graduate school most of the approximately 14000 indian students 
who take the gre each year are trying to gain admittance to us 
graduate schools 
ets which administers standardized tests in 170 countries said 
it had canceled the scores of 2744 of 4280 test takers for the 
gre administered oct 14 at 17 of 27 indian test centers 
it said it was rescheduling the dec 9 gre in india to next 
month 
an estimated 366000 students worldwide take the gre each year 
according to ets 
