<TEXT>
sir john pritchard a leading international 
conductor and musical director of san franciscos opera has died 
of lung cancer he was 68 
pritchard died tuesday at seton medical center 
pritchard was among britains highestpaid busiest and most 
distinguished conductors and was knighted in 1983 by queen 
elizabeth ii for his contribution to british musical life 
his last public appearance in britain was sept 16 when he 
conducted the bbc symphony orchestra on the popular last night of 
the annual promenade concerts at the royal albert hall in london 
an announcer told concertgoers that pritchard had not been well and 
he sat while conducting 
he was chief conductor of the bbc symphony from 1982 until 
october and of the cologne opera in west germany from 1978 until 
this summer 
he had been musical director of the san francisco opera since 
1986 and held the same post at glyndebourne the english opera 
house and the theater de la monnaie in brussels 
he was only 31 when he was invited to conduct at the vienna 
state opera in 195253 and composer benjamin britten chose him to 
condut his 1953 opera gloriana for queen elizabeth iis 
coronation 
pritchard conducted this seasons new production of mozarts 
idomeneo a work on which he was a leading authority illness 
forced him to cancel this falls performances of puccinis madame 
butterfly and vivaldis orlando furioso his tenure was 
supposed to have ended in 1990 
pritchard never married burial will be in sussex england near 
glyndebourne 
a memorial is set for monday at san franciscos grace cathedral 
