<TEXT>
canadian pacific ltd said it intends to spin 
off its real estate portfolio valued at more than 3 billion and 
has adopted an antitakeover defense 
president william stinson said tuesday that the company knew of 
no takeover threats but decided to adopt a poison pill as a 
preemptive measure 
rumors circulated last summer about an impending takeover of the 
montrealbased conglomerate which has interests in numerous aspects 
of the canadian economy including transportation energy forest 
products telecommunications and real estate 
analysts say canadian pacific would be rich pickings for a 
raider with an eye on dismantling it possible buyers mentioned in 
rumors were the british conglomerate hanson plc and montreals paul 
desmarais president of cashrich power corp 
canadian pacific plans to spin off its marathon realty co 
turning it into a publicly traded company eighty percent of 
marathon will be distributed to canadian pacific shareholders and 
the remaining 20 percent will be retained by canadian pacific 
which will help marathon in developing the potential of its 
property holdings 
the distribution was approved in principle by canadian pacifics 
board of directors on tuesday the plan will be implemented once it 
is approved by shareholders and after certain other conditions are 
met 
canadian pacific said the book value of marathons assets is 
about 21 canadian dollars but internal estimates indicate its 
current market value exceeds 4 billion canadian dollars or about 
343 billion 
meanwhile the company also announced tuesday that upon the 
occurrence of certain triggering events stockholders will have 
the right to acquire shares at 50 per cent of market value a move 
that would significantly dilute stock value 
the events include acquisition of 10 per cent or more of 
ordinary shares or of ordinary and preferred shares by a buyer 
who doesnt have approval from the board of directors 
canadian pacific said the aim of the plan is to ensure 
shareholders get the most for their stock under any takeover 
stinson at a gathering of financial analysts in toronto 
emphasized the posion pill is a preemptive measure and he is not 
aware of any pending or threatened takeover bids for the company 
i dont know of any action in the stock that would suggest an 
impending takeover its been quiet of late he said 
poison pills used for the first time in canada by inco ltd 
last fall but widely prevalent in the united states are aimed at 
discouraging hostile takeovers by burdening a company with debt or 
triggering a dilution of stock 
canadian pacifics poison pill must be approved at the companys 
annual meeting next may 
canadian pacific shares closed on the toronto stock exchange on 
tuesday at 2512 canadian dollars down 12 cents 
